1
00:00:01,440 --> 00:00:03,780
(Episode 78)

2
00:00:04,380 --> 00:00:05,440
What do we do?

3
00:00:06,710 --> 00:00:08,610
I guess they found out
about the kidnapping already.

4
00:00:13,050 --> 00:00:14,120
Chae Hwa Young.

5
00:00:14,820 --> 00:00:17,320
You're under arrest
for the murder of Oh Bok Gil.

6
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:21,360
But...

7
00:00:42,910 --> 00:00:46,120
You have the right to an attorney
and the right to remain silent.

8
00:00:46,120 --> 00:00:48,550
- However, this may work against you.
- Hold on.

9
00:00:49,690 --> 00:00:51,060
Let me see the arrest warrant.

10
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,360
(Arrest Warrant)

11
00:00:59,930 --> 00:01:01,000
Wait, what...

12
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:02,800
CEO Chae!

13
00:01:03,670 --> 00:01:04,840
Murder? You?

14
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:07,370
- What is all this?
- Honey,

15
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:09,140
- Oh my, Grandfather!
- calm down.

16
00:01:09,410 --> 00:01:13,180
Here, sit down. Sit down right here.

17
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:15,610
Oh my goodness, what is happening? Murder?

18
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:18,650
Chae Hwa Young, due to the risk
of you fleeing or destroying evidence,

19
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:21,990
we're placing you under emergency arrest
under Criminal Code Article 200-2.

20
00:01:22,590 --> 00:01:23,590
Let's go.

21
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:27,690
Oh Bok Gil? Who's that?

22
00:01:28,130 --> 00:01:30,900
This is a total setup!
Take these handcuffs off me right now!

23
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,600
Or I'll make sure every single
one of you is fired!

24
00:01:34,670 --> 00:01:37,570
So the video of you abusing your power
was true after all.

25
00:01:38,870 --> 00:01:40,740
Should I add obstruction
of a public official to your charges?

26
00:01:41,340 --> 00:01:45,440
- It wasn't me! I'm being framed!
- CEO Chae!

27
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:48,950
Go to the station and find out
what this is all about!

28
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:53,820
- Honey, should I call Dr. Kim?
- No, it's not that serious.

29
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:57,760
You know Oh Jang Mi well, don't you?

30
00:01:58,490 --> 00:01:59,560
You two met often, didn't you?

31
00:02:00,090 --> 00:02:01,160
I don't know her.

32
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:04,760
Oh Jang Mi? The one Baek Ho
was always talking about...

33
00:02:05,630 --> 00:02:08,470
- Oh my.
- Oh Bok Gil is Oh Jang Mi's father.

34
00:02:08,470 --> 00:02:09,930
Does that ring a bell?

35
00:02:10,540 --> 00:02:12,840
You sent flowers
and condolence money to the funeral.

36
00:02:13,570 --> 00:02:15,210
You aren't going to pretend
you don't remember, are you?

37
00:02:15,770 --> 00:02:17,410
I've already heard the whole story
from the family.

38
00:02:20,380 --> 00:02:22,950
That's ridiculous!
I told you, I don't know anything!

39
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:25,820
Do you have any idea
how many people I help?

40
00:02:26,150 --> 00:02:29,290
Besides, that case is already closed!

41
00:02:29,820 --> 00:02:32,420
Why are you dragging me into this now
when I have nothing to do with it?

42
00:02:32,890 --> 00:02:35,660
Funny how you don't know him,
but you know the case was closed.

43
00:02:36,330 --> 00:02:38,230
New evidence has come to light.

44
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:39,860
What evidence?

45
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:41,370
Come on, let's go.

46
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:44,940
No! I don't know anything!
No! What evidence?

47
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,970
There can't be any! That's impossible!

48
00:02:47,010 --> 00:02:50,740
You can see for yourself at the station
whether there's evidence or not.

49
00:02:51,140 --> 00:02:52,310
- No.
- Let's go.

50
00:02:52,340 --> 00:02:55,910
No! I don't know anything! I don't!

51
00:02:56,010 --> 00:02:58,320
Gosh, I don't know! Father!

52
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,180
- Let go of me! Let go right now...
- CEO Chae!

53
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:03,250
Lawyer!

54
00:03:03,890 --> 00:03:06,260
Manager Lee! Call my lawyer, now!

55
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:09,390
And hire someone
even better than Kang Baek Ho!

56
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:14,000
Lee Kang Hyuk, we have questions for you,
so come with us to the station.

57
00:03:16,730 --> 00:03:20,640
No. I'm being framed. I'm telling you.
There's no way you have anything.

58
00:03:20,770 --> 00:03:23,110
Darn it, I'm innocent!
Father, it wasn't me.

59
00:03:23,170 --> 00:03:26,840
It wasn't me! Father! Please!
It really wasn't me!

60
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:34,950
Dad. We can finally get justice...

61
00:03:35,420 --> 00:03:37,260
for your wrongful death.

62
00:03:38,060 --> 00:03:39,060
Dad.

63
00:03:46,730 --> 00:03:48,970
Reporter Kim,
I've got a huge scoop for you!

64
00:03:49,230 --> 00:03:53,840
I'm only giving this tip to you,
so get over here! Go now!

65
00:03:54,010 --> 00:03:58,210
Reporter Lee, I've got a huge scoop!
Reporter Choi, big scoop here!

66
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:03,750
I think that's them.

67
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:07,150
- What? Isn't that them?
- Get out of the car now.

68
00:04:08,220 --> 00:04:12,060
- Do you admit to the murder charges?
- Coming through! Back up!

69
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,120
CEO Chae, do you admit to the murder?

70
00:04:13,190 --> 00:04:15,990
- Please give us a statement!
- CEO, are the murder allegations true?

71
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:18,630
Please say something!
You have to tell us the truth!

72
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:22,000
- CEO Chae Hwa Young!
- It wasn't me! This is a setup!

73
00:04:22,130 --> 00:04:25,000
- It's all a misunderstanding!
- All right, we're coming through!

74
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,710
- CEO Chae Hwa Young!
- It wasn't me. I'm innocent.

75
00:04:27,770 --> 00:04:29,240
- Just one word...
- I'm innocent.

76
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:30,510
- Please tell us the truth.
- No!

77
00:04:30,910 --> 00:04:33,180
- I'm innocent! I said no!
- Hey, get the shot!

78
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:34,250
Just give us one comment, please.

79
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:39,880
Honey! Come here, quick!

80
00:04:40,690 --> 00:04:41,790
Gosh.

81
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:45,460
Chae Hwa Young, CEO of Dream Hotel...

82
00:04:45,460 --> 00:04:47,090
and a key figure in Dream Group,
was arrested today...

83
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:49,530
- on suspicion of murder.
- Oh my goodness.

84
00:04:49,530 --> 00:04:52,860
- What's all the fuss about?
- It was considered a car accident...

85
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:56,770
after a local professor, Kang,
turned himself in and confessed.

86
00:04:56,900 --> 00:05:00,510
The case involving Mr. Oh's death
had already been closed.

87
00:05:00,870 --> 00:05:05,210
But new, crucial evidence has surfaced
that could overturn the initial ruling...

88
00:05:05,340 --> 00:05:09,510
and as a result, CEO Chae Hwa Young
has been named as the mastermind.

89
00:05:09,710 --> 00:05:13,950
- The professor from that university,
- Police believe CEO Chae is involved...

90
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:15,020
- that's you.
- in this case and are investigating...

91
00:05:15,020 --> 00:05:16,250
the suspect's specific motive...

92
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:20,390
Then what Baek Ho said back then
was actually true?

93
00:05:20,390 --> 00:05:21,530
The case that was almost buried...

94
00:05:21,690 --> 00:05:25,830
Chae Hwa Young, CEO of Dream Hotel
and a major player in the business world,

95
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:28,030
has been arrested on suspicion of murder.

96
00:05:28,270 --> 00:05:31,640
The case was closed after Professor Kang
from a local university confessed,

97
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:36,540
but with new evidence recently surfacing
in the death of Mr. Oh,

98
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:38,810
- investigators are weighing...
- Oh my.

99
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:41,510
- the possibility of a premeditated crime.
- What on earth is this all about?

100
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:45,250
So Professor Kang Nam Bong's accident
wasn't an accident,

101
00:05:45,820 --> 00:05:48,150
but a murder orchestrated
by Chae Hwa Young?

102
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:53,830
- Chairman.
- So? Did you find out anything?

103
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:56,830
Right, let's go in.

104
00:05:57,530 --> 00:05:58,530
Yes, sir.

105
00:06:02,430 --> 00:06:06,500
Gosh, this looks like a really big deal.

106
00:06:08,010 --> 00:06:11,140
So Chae Hwa Young is a murderer?

107
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,440
Gosh, that gives me the creeps.

108
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:17,250
Chae Hwa Young, CEO of Dream Hotel
and a key figure in Dream Group,

109
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:20,180
was arrested today on suspicion of murder.

110
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,120
Dad.

111
00:06:23,860 --> 00:06:24,920
It took a while,

112
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:28,230
but we finally caught the person
who killed you.

113
00:06:28,230 --> 00:06:29,890
The case in which the victim,
Mr. Oh, was murdered...

114
00:06:29,930 --> 00:06:31,030
I'm so sorry, Dad.

115
00:06:35,970 --> 00:06:36,970
Hello, Tae Pyung.

116
00:06:37,340 --> 00:06:39,400
Hey, Jang Mi. I'll put Mom on.

117
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:43,210
Jang Mi. Sweetie, I heard you were sick.

118
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:45,810
Are you okay, honey?

119
00:06:46,110 --> 00:06:49,480
Yes, look, Mom. See? I'm perfectly fine.

120
00:06:50,650 --> 00:06:51,780
Now let me look at you.

121
00:06:52,380 --> 00:06:54,250
Are you okay, Mom?
Are you hurting anywhere?

122
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:57,960
Suk Hee is fine.
Suk Hee isn't sick anymore.

123
00:06:58,090 --> 00:07:00,890
Come on, Mom.
You still look a little pale.

124
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:05,460
Mom, you saw they caught her, right?
You saw them dragging her to the station.

125
00:07:05,530 --> 00:07:08,070
Yes, Chae Hwa Young is bad.

126
00:07:08,230 --> 00:07:12,470
- The police arrested her just like that.
- Yes, that's right.

127
00:07:13,370 --> 00:07:15,710
I hope this means they can clear
your name too, Mom.

128
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:20,080
Mom, are you okay?

129
00:07:20,340 --> 00:07:22,850
Tae Pyung, shouldn't we take Mom
back to the hospital?

130
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:27,450
No, Suk Hee is fine. Suk Hee isn't sick.

131
00:07:27,990 --> 00:07:31,560
- Mom.
- I'll watch and take her in if needed.

132
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:34,260
You should hang up.
What if your coworkers see you?

133
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,560
Okay.

134
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:37,430
Please take good care of Mom
for me, Tae Pyung.

135
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:42,770
Mom, just wait a little longer.
I'll come home with all your favorites.

136
00:07:43,270 --> 00:07:46,970
Jang Mi, come home soon.
My pretty Jang Mi.

137
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,480
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

138
00:07:54,610 --> 00:07:57,280
I saw your mother this morning,
so don't worry too much.

139
00:07:57,880 --> 00:08:00,320
She still has a bit of a cold,
but she seemed fine otherwise.

140
00:08:00,790 --> 00:08:03,420
I want to go back to my mom
more than anything.

141
00:08:03,820 --> 00:08:06,360
I know. This time, it won't be easy...

142
00:08:06,660 --> 00:08:09,130
for CEO Chae to escape this,
no matter how much she denies it.

143
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:10,390
I hope you're right.

144
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:12,230
I've been thinking.

145
00:08:12,530 --> 00:08:16,700
Now that Chae Hwa Young is caught,
I should tell the Chairman the truth.

146
00:08:17,470 --> 00:08:19,670
The Chairman needs to know what she did.

147
00:08:20,340 --> 00:08:23,070
Just break it to him gently
so he won't be too shocked.

148
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:28,150
Team Leader Jin. Do you really think
CEO Chae committed murder?

149
00:08:28,610 --> 00:08:32,150
I know. We should have known ever since
that video of her power trip went viral.

150
00:08:35,290 --> 00:08:36,790
My apologies, Director Ma.

151
00:08:45,730 --> 00:08:47,670
Thanks to you, Hong Ju,
I was able to get an exclusive.

152
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:49,100
Thanks for the tip.

153
00:08:54,510 --> 00:08:56,640
Director Ma, are you okay?

154
00:08:59,980 --> 00:09:01,710
This is so humiliating. I can't stay here.

155
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:03,580
I'm heading out.

156
00:09:09,350 --> 00:09:10,350
Chae Hwa Young.

157
00:09:10,890 --> 00:09:12,390
I'll ask you again.

158
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:15,630
The night of the incident, where were you?

159
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:30,680
Manager Lee being released must mean...

160
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:34,010
We've confirmed
Manager Lee Kang Hyuk's alibi.

161
00:09:35,050 --> 00:09:36,210
An alibi?

162
00:09:36,650 --> 00:09:37,650
Chae Hwa Young.

163
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:41,450
You put the victim, Oh Bok Gil, in the car
and took him to the scene, didn't you?

164
00:09:41,620 --> 00:09:45,790
Then you called Kang Nam Bong.
Or did you two conspire to do this?

165
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:49,390
Chae Hwa Young.

166
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:52,330
Refusing to make a statement
will only work against you.

167
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,200
Start talking.

168
00:09:54,470 --> 00:09:57,970
- Why did you kill Oh Bok Gil?
- Kill him? That's ridiculous.

169
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,840
He was pestering me, so I pushed him.

170
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:05,240
Then he made a scene
and hit his head on his own.

171
00:10:05,710 --> 00:10:07,380
Then he started demanding money,

172
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:09,980
so I gave him cash for his medical bills
and sent him on his way.

173
00:10:10,550 --> 00:10:11,550
That's all there is to it.

174
00:10:12,420 --> 00:10:14,820
After that, I left for a meeting.

175
00:10:15,790 --> 00:10:17,790
I found out he died from the news.

176
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:22,430
I didn't say anything
because it didn't happen at the hotel.

177
00:10:22,490 --> 00:10:25,460
Look, Chae Hwa Young,
why do you keep lying to me?

178
00:10:25,530 --> 00:10:28,770
It's the truth! I'm telling you,
I was at the office!

179
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:31,870
I was in a meeting
with the board members until late.

180
00:10:31,940 --> 00:10:36,270
However, cell tower data shows
you weren't at the office.

181
00:10:39,210 --> 00:10:43,110
The signals from
both Oh Bok Gil's phone and yours...

182
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:48,150
were tracked moving from the Dream Hotel
to the crime scene...

183
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:49,820
at the exact same time.

184
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:53,720
Now, are you still going to deny it?

185
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:55,860
I have no idea what you're talking about.

186
00:10:56,660 --> 00:10:59,000
Why would my phone have been there?

187
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,730
I must have lost my phone.

188
00:11:02,070 --> 00:11:04,470
On top of that, the location
where you called Kang Nam Bong...

189
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:07,940
- was the scene of the traffic accident.
- I told you, I lost it!

190
00:11:08,540 --> 00:11:11,610
That case was closed ages ago.
Why are you digging this up now?

191
00:11:15,910 --> 00:11:19,450
Then why were you in possession
of Oh Bok Gil's cell phone?

192
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:20,890
His cell phone?

193
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:25,590
Then, does that mean
Oh Jang Mi gave me a fake?

194
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:28,730
That sneaky little wench tricked me?

195
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:33,100
You keeping Oh Bok Gil's phone
in your safe is...

196
00:11:33,630 --> 00:11:38,000
circumstantial proof you met him
on the day of the incident.

197
00:11:39,100 --> 00:11:40,100
Chae Hwa Young.

198
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:44,910
- Just confess already, okay?
- I don't know anything!

199
00:11:45,380 --> 00:11:48,150
What do you think you can do to me
with such flimsy circumstantial evidence?

200
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:51,850
Oh, really? Then should I show you
some more conclusive evidence?

201
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:55,390
There's a video with a clear shot
of your face in it.

202
00:11:55,550 --> 00:11:57,520
From the very moment Oh Bok Gil collapsed.

203
00:11:58,460 --> 00:11:59,490
And other physical evidence as well.

204
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:02,690
- So, it's all...
- Here. See for yourself.

205
00:12:05,030 --> 00:12:08,170
Now, there's no explaining this away,
is there?

206
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:10,840
This video is from the day
Oh Bok Gil died.

207
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:15,840
This is when, intentionally or not,
you killed Oh Bok Gil,

208
00:12:16,610 --> 00:12:17,780
and left him on the side of the road.

209
00:12:18,510 --> 00:12:19,810
You staged it to look like a car accident.

210
00:12:20,380 --> 00:12:22,380
I already told you what happened!

211
00:12:23,950 --> 00:12:28,320
First, we need to confirm whether
this was an accident from a simple fight.

212
00:12:28,490 --> 00:12:33,160
It's not confirmed if Mr. Oh went there
on his own or if he was moved.

213
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:37,290
Therefore, you cannot say that
Chae Hwa Young caused Oh Bok Gil's death.

214
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:40,800
I expected you to argue that,

215
00:12:41,100 --> 00:12:45,800
but she concealed crucial evidence,
and when Ms. Oh took that evidence,

216
00:12:45,940 --> 00:12:49,140
she had Jung Suk Hee kidnapped,
and even blackmailed her.

217
00:12:51,410 --> 00:12:52,910
You're a flight risk,

218
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:58,120
and with a history of destroying evidence,
the charges are piling up.

219
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:00,480
Your arrest and detention are unavoidable.

220
00:13:01,020 --> 00:13:05,290
- You know that as well as I do, counsel.
- No! I'm not a murderer!

221
00:13:06,090 --> 00:13:08,930
A key figure in Dream Group,
CEO Chae Hwa Young of Dream Hotel,

222
00:13:08,990 --> 00:13:12,860
- was arrested today on murder charges.
- That's insane.

223
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:16,770
- Murder?
- At the time, local Professor Kang...

224
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:19,040
This can't be happening.

225
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:21,540
And to think her blood
runs through my veins.

226
00:13:27,380 --> 00:13:28,380
Hey, you saw the news, right?

227
00:13:30,280 --> 00:13:31,280
Is it true?

228
00:13:32,250 --> 00:13:34,050
The "Professor Kang" on the news.

229
00:13:34,450 --> 00:13:36,690
- That's our father.
- What?

230
00:13:37,020 --> 00:13:38,290
No, how could Father possibly...

231
00:13:39,190 --> 00:13:41,430
- cover for what CEO Chae did?
- I'm telling you because we're brothers.

232
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:47,300
- I think CEO Chae used Dad.
- Make it make sense.

233
00:13:48,100 --> 00:13:50,100
Dad's not a three-year-old kid.

234
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:53,170
How could he possibly take the fall
for a murder?

235
00:13:53,370 --> 00:13:55,740
Jang Mi's father was in
the Dream Hotel parking garage...

236
00:13:56,110 --> 00:13:58,280
and he collapsed during an argument
with CEO Chae.

237
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:02,450
So CEO Chae needed someone
to take the fall for her.

238
00:14:03,450 --> 00:14:06,020
- And Dad was caught in the crossfire.
- So you're saying...

239
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:09,950
you think Dad walked right into a trap
set by CEO Chae?

240
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:11,660
It's not a theory, it's a fact.

241
00:14:12,060 --> 00:14:14,390
There's video of him collapsing
during his argument with CEO Chae.

242
00:14:14,590 --> 00:14:16,530
But what about moving him
to the crash site?

243
00:14:16,530 --> 00:14:17,660
You didn't see that part, did you?

244
00:14:17,730 --> 00:14:21,700
- Don't tell me you're taking her side.
- That's not it.

245
00:14:22,270 --> 00:14:24,070
I'm just saying it doesn't make any sense.

246
00:14:24,130 --> 00:14:28,040
Back then, Dad turned himself in,
so they didn't investigate thoroughly.

247
00:14:28,670 --> 00:14:32,040
But now that there's video evidence,
everything will come to light.

248
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:36,080
Dad's name will finally be cleared.

249
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:41,990
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

250
00:14:43,420 --> 00:14:44,420
Manager Lee.

251
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:48,630
- General Manager Kang.
- Is that breaking news true?

252
00:14:49,190 --> 00:14:51,200
- Did CEO Chae really...
- No, she didn't.

253
00:14:52,630 --> 00:14:55,330
- It is absolutely not true.
- But they're saying there's a video.

254
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,400
It's a setup.

255
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:00,840
I will get CEO Chae out of this,
so please don't worry.

256
00:15:02,410 --> 00:15:03,970
Tell me everything, the whole truth.

257
00:15:04,710 --> 00:15:06,310
How else am I supposed to help?

258
00:15:06,610 --> 00:15:07,710
All you need to do is...

259
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:11,420
trust CEO Chae.

260
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:13,750
If you'll excuse me.

261
00:15:18,190 --> 00:15:20,190
And yet, there's clear video evidence.

262
00:15:22,790 --> 00:15:25,530
You're the one who called the reporters
to get CEO Chae on the news?

263
00:15:25,730 --> 00:15:27,630
I saw my chance and jumped on it.

264
00:15:28,030 --> 00:15:31,970
Reporter Kim really owes me for the scoop.
He said he's treating me to a huge dinner.

265
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:35,240
Hong Ju, you're so clever.

266
00:15:35,470 --> 00:15:37,570
You were so quick on your feet.
That was brilliant.

267
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:40,780
I was so shocked
that my hands were trembling.

268
00:15:40,780 --> 00:15:42,610
I couldn't even think straight.

269
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:44,320
What did the Chairman have to say?

270
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:47,650
He's not still going to protect CEO Chae
after all this, is he?

271
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:50,250
He's been shut in his study
with Secretary Kim all day,

272
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:51,920
running a cost-benefit analysis.

273
00:15:52,190 --> 00:15:54,990
That man is really something else.

274
00:15:55,460 --> 00:15:58,500
With all this talk of murder,
how can he be so calm and collected?

275
00:15:58,730 --> 00:16:02,070
- It honestly gives me the creeps.
- He's the Chairman for a reason.

276
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:03,170
You've got a point.

277
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:08,170
To run a company that big,
I'm sure the Chairman has seen it all.

278
00:16:08,510 --> 00:16:11,480
Anyway, seeing CEO Chae
get hauled away in handcuffs felt like...

279
00:16:11,710 --> 00:16:14,010
a weight I'd carried for ten years
was finally lifted off my shoulders.

280
00:16:14,310 --> 00:16:16,410
- Right, Mom?
- Tell me about it!

281
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:21,420
It was so satisfying.
I feel lighter than I have in years.

282
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:29,890
What have you done to be kneeling
like this? Get up already!

283
00:16:30,090 --> 00:16:32,200
Why would you ever kneel
before your grandfather?

284
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:34,030
Grandfather.

285
00:16:36,330 --> 00:16:37,430
This is my chance.

286
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:40,100
I have to tell him the secret
that I'm Seo Rin's twin.

287
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:43,870
To expose how monstrous Chae Hwa Young is,
I have to tell him now.

288
00:16:47,380 --> 00:16:48,380
Grandfather,

289
00:16:49,410 --> 00:16:50,950
there's something I need to tell you.

290
00:16:51,580 --> 00:16:52,680
Without holding anything back,

291
00:16:53,380 --> 00:16:54,650
I'm going to tell you everything.

292
00:16:55,090 --> 00:16:57,550
All right,
let's hear what you have to say.

293
00:16:57,820 --> 00:16:59,460
Come on, get up.

294
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:01,130
Let's go into my study.

295
00:17:04,130 --> 00:17:06,730
Do you think Seo Rin knows she's a twin?

296
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:07,900
I doubt it.

297
00:17:08,830 --> 00:17:11,140
Knowing her, she'd have gone ballistic
by now if she knew.

298
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:15,840
- So Seo Rin knew her mom was a murderer?
- Oh my.

299
00:17:22,780 --> 00:17:23,780
All right.

300
00:17:24,620 --> 00:17:26,720
What is it you wanted to tell me?

301
00:17:28,190 --> 00:17:30,850
All this time, did you know...

302
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:35,190
what your mother was doing?

303
00:17:37,490 --> 00:17:38,500
Did you?

304
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:43,730
You knew, didn't you?
About her dirty work.

305
00:17:48,670 --> 00:17:50,670
Chairman, we have a huge problem.

306
00:17:52,510 --> 00:17:53,510
It can't be...

307
00:17:55,310 --> 00:17:58,480
- Grandfather.
- Chairman! The doctor said to be careful.

308
00:17:58,550 --> 00:18:02,290
- He said not to get worked up.
- No, I'm fine.

309
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:05,520
What's wrong?

310
00:18:05,860 --> 00:18:09,330
As soon as the news about CEO Chae broke,
the shareholders have been in an uproar.

311
00:18:10,030 --> 00:18:11,330
The moment the market opens tomorrow,

312
00:18:11,700 --> 00:18:14,160
there's talk that our stock
is going to plummet.

313
00:18:17,170 --> 00:18:19,870
- It was bound to happen.
- What are we going to do, honey?

314
00:18:20,270 --> 00:18:22,770
Is Dream Group going to go under
at this rate?

315
00:18:23,010 --> 00:18:26,840
Major shareholders are already preparing
to dump their shares.

316
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,980
The market sentiment
is getting really ugly.

317
00:18:30,850 --> 00:18:32,280
Oh my, Grandfather!

318
00:18:32,580 --> 00:18:35,650
- Oh no.
- We need to call Dr. Kim.

319
00:18:36,390 --> 00:18:38,760
- Next up is the death of the victim,
- I'm home.

320
00:18:38,820 --> 00:18:40,060
Mr. Oh, a case
that had already been closed.

321
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:42,860
During the investigation, several pieces
of new evidence were found...

322
00:18:42,930 --> 00:18:46,060
that were decisive enough
to overturn the initial ruling,

323
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:48,270
pointing to CEO Chae Hwa Young
as the mastermind behind the incident...

324
00:18:52,070 --> 00:18:53,440
So what happens now?

325
00:18:54,140 --> 00:18:55,640
Of all the rotten luck,
the men in our family...

326
00:18:56,340 --> 00:18:58,610
all work for Dream Group.

327
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:01,450
I thought you were glad they worked there.

328
00:19:01,450 --> 00:19:02,680
I was.

329
00:19:04,550 --> 00:19:05,550
But still, surely...

330
00:19:06,350 --> 00:19:09,550
the company won't get shaken up
just because of what the CEO did, right?

331
00:19:09,620 --> 00:19:13,560
Dream Group probably won't collapse.
The company's too solid.

332
00:19:13,790 --> 00:19:16,290
And CEO Chae's charges are still
under investigation,

333
00:19:17,860 --> 00:19:19,830
so we'll have to wait
and see what happens.

334
00:19:20,060 --> 00:19:23,670
I was so excited about our son
marrying into that family.

335
00:19:24,170 --> 00:19:25,840
We really dodged a bullet there.

336
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:29,170
Who would've thought CEO Chae
was that kind of person?

337
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:31,040
It's horrifying.

338
00:19:31,380 --> 00:19:34,080
Things like that are a product
of circumstance.

339
00:19:37,350 --> 00:19:41,290
Nothing has been definitively proven yet.

340
00:19:41,450 --> 00:19:42,450
Dad,

341
00:19:42,990 --> 00:19:46,660
even with the video evidence,
you still seem to be on CEO Chae's side.

342
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:50,030
On her side?
What are you talking about, son?

343
00:19:50,890 --> 00:19:52,030
I'm just saying, is all.

344
00:19:52,100 --> 00:19:55,530
I'll give her
the benefit of the doubt for now,

345
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,230
but if CEO Chae...

346
00:19:58,140 --> 00:20:00,370
tried to pin this on you,

347
00:20:01,910 --> 00:20:03,770
I won't let that woman get away with it.

348
00:20:04,470 --> 00:20:06,610
- What?
- For damages.

349
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:10,510
I'm suing her for an astronomical amount,
so tell her to be prepared.

350
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:15,450
Why should you get entangled with her
and be framed for her crime?

351
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:16,890
It just doesn't make any sense.

352
00:20:17,490 --> 00:20:19,360
The more I think about it,
the more despicable she seems.

353
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:26,100
Anyway, what's going to
happen to CEO Chae?

354
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:29,230
The evidence is solid.
She'll be detained during the probe.

355
00:20:30,870 --> 00:20:31,870
Is that so?

356
00:20:38,810 --> 00:20:41,310
The Chairman's blood pressure is unstable,

357
00:20:41,780 --> 00:20:44,150
so he must avoid any shocks
for the time being.

358
00:20:44,950 --> 00:20:46,580
He needs complete bed rest.

359
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:49,650
Grandfather.

360
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:52,620
You have to be strong.

361
00:20:57,130 --> 00:20:58,500
Don't you worry.

362
00:20:59,060 --> 00:21:00,130
My dear girl.

363
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:04,840
I have to see you get married...

364
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:07,540
and have kids of your own
before I can die.

365
00:21:08,670 --> 00:21:10,610
I'm not dying anytime soon.

366
00:21:11,410 --> 00:21:12,440
Oh, goodness.

367
00:21:12,940 --> 00:21:14,280
Of course.

368
00:21:14,580 --> 00:21:16,580
You have to live a long life...

369
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:19,820
so that I can keep on living too.

370
00:21:31,530 --> 00:21:33,830
So I take it
you couldn't tell the Chairman.

371
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:37,300
Right. He can't handle the shock.

372
00:21:38,340 --> 00:21:41,510
I can always tell him
about the twin story later.

373
00:21:42,370 --> 00:21:45,340
Right now, shareholders are in an uproar
because of CEO Chae.

374
00:21:45,810 --> 00:21:47,880
The Chairman must be worried sick.

375
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:51,110
- He needs to get his health back first.
- I'm just so upset.

376
00:21:51,450 --> 00:21:54,250
I had no idea Chae Hwa Young had
that much influence over the company.

377
00:21:59,220 --> 00:22:01,190
Jang Mi, it's about Chae Hwa Young.

378
00:22:01,530 --> 00:22:03,790
I just heard the prosecutor's office
issued an arrest warrant for her.

379
00:22:04,930 --> 00:22:06,630
So she's going straight
to a detention center?

380
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:07,960
She won't be getting out anytime soon.

381
00:22:09,930 --> 00:22:11,070
You've been through a lot, Jang Mi.

382
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:14,570
It's all thanks to you, Baek Ho.

383
00:22:22,350 --> 00:22:23,550
Step forward.

384
00:22:25,780 --> 00:22:28,620
Head up. Look straight into the camera.

385
00:22:28,690 --> 00:22:30,520
(6620, Chae Hwa Young)

386
00:22:43,670 --> 00:22:44,670
(Korea Correctional Service)

387
00:22:49,340 --> 00:22:51,640
Well, well, look who it is.

388
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:55,580
Isn't that the old cover girl
we used to see on TV?

389
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:58,010
I heard you only stay at five-star hotels.

390
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:01,420
What brings you to a dump like this?

391
00:23:07,660 --> 00:23:12,430
But there's no room service here.
What will you do?

392
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:15,670
Why don't you put on a little show for us?

393
00:23:15,730 --> 00:23:18,670
- Yes, room service sounds great.
- Don't you dare.

394
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,270
I'm on a completely different
level than you.

395
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:24,540
I'll be out of here in no time.
So you'd better watch yourselves.

396
00:23:25,540 --> 00:23:30,310
Hey, she says we're not on her level.
My gosh.

397
00:23:31,010 --> 00:23:32,220
Getting out soon?

398
00:23:33,380 --> 00:23:34,380
Hey.

399
00:23:35,050 --> 00:23:39,560
Aren't you in for murder?
And didn't you tamper with evidence, too?

400
00:23:39,720 --> 00:23:42,760
Hey, that's a life sentence, you know?

401
00:23:43,060 --> 00:23:46,330
Let us give you a taste
of our "different league."

402
00:23:47,630 --> 00:23:48,670
Pathetic.

403
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:54,810
Well now, CEO.
Your fingernails are just gorgeous.

404
00:23:55,210 --> 00:23:57,470
It'd be a shame
if they got all messed up tonight.

405
00:24:00,410 --> 00:24:04,880
I'll have you all charged with insults
and make you rot in here. You hear me?

406
00:24:06,150 --> 00:24:09,050
- Give me a break.
- Listen to the mouth on her.

407
00:24:09,350 --> 00:24:11,720
Hey, new face.

408
00:24:12,360 --> 00:24:14,490
I guess you wouldn't know
since you've never had it,

409
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:17,190
but we don't get beans and rice
anymore here.

410
00:24:17,230 --> 00:24:21,100
But if you're so desperate for some,

411
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:23,430
I guess we can just eat your food for you.

412
00:24:24,630 --> 00:24:25,840
Gosh, you little...

413
00:24:26,400 --> 00:24:27,770
Who does she think she is,
acting high and mighty?

414
00:24:27,900 --> 00:24:31,840
- What's going on here? Break it up, now.
- This isn't over.

415
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:33,540
Lucky you.

416
00:24:33,710 --> 00:24:38,550
Get me my lawyer, now!

417
00:24:38,620 --> 00:24:39,980
Now!

418
00:24:41,850 --> 00:24:44,690
This can't be happening.
It has to be a dream.

419
00:24:44,960 --> 00:24:47,790
This is a nightmare!

420
00:24:48,630 --> 00:24:50,490
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

421
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:51,960
How is Director Ma doing?

422
00:24:52,260 --> 00:24:55,230
The Chairman is ill,
so she's looking after him.

423
00:24:56,130 --> 00:24:58,470
But about Oh Jang Mi's father...

424
00:24:58,840 --> 00:25:02,470
- Is it true that CEO Chae killed him?
- No, it's not.

425
00:25:02,910 --> 00:25:05,810
But they say
there's definitive video evidence.

426
00:25:06,040 --> 00:25:07,880
That's why she was arrested.

427
00:25:09,280 --> 00:25:12,880
Let's have faith in CEO Chae and wait.
We shouldn't get swept up in all this.

428
00:25:13,780 --> 00:25:14,780
What?

429
00:25:16,350 --> 00:25:17,350
Okay.

430
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:20,890
You know, Jun Ho is something else.

431
00:25:21,420 --> 00:25:23,690
He used to despise CEO Chae,

432
00:25:23,690 --> 00:25:26,030
but now that
she may be his future mother-in-law,

433
00:25:26,300 --> 00:25:29,300
he said we should trust CEO Chae
and wait. Can you believe that?

434
00:25:30,030 --> 00:25:31,300
How ridiculous.

435
00:25:31,570 --> 00:25:34,500
I get that he's after the money,
but defending a murderer is going too far.

436
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:37,970
Besides, the Chairman doesn't intend
to approve that marriage,

437
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:40,540
but he's already counting his chickens,
don't you think?

438
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:43,350
Mom, how's the Chairman doing, by the way?

439
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:45,920
He seems to be getting better now.

440
00:25:46,180 --> 00:25:48,620
But he shouldn't be put
under any more stress.

441
00:25:49,350 --> 00:25:51,490
Anyway, even after all this,

442
00:25:51,820 --> 00:25:53,690
he's not going to keep defending
CEO Chae, is he?

443
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:57,730
Hey. Give me the blanket.

444
00:25:58,230 --> 00:26:00,600
- Gosh.
- Get over here!

445
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:02,300
Right there.

446
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:10,070
- Guards! Help me!
- Darn it! You witch!

447
00:26:10,810 --> 00:26:11,810
Hey, cover her up!

448
00:26:14,110 --> 00:26:16,950
- Gosh, darn it!
- Hey!

449
00:26:17,010 --> 00:26:18,010
Gosh, darn it!

450
00:26:18,280 --> 00:26:21,180
- You little...
- Gosh, this one's really something.

451
00:26:21,480 --> 00:26:24,350
- Darn...
- Guess you won't learn without a beating.

452
00:26:24,420 --> 00:26:27,460
I'm getting out of here.
I swear I'm getting out.

453
00:26:28,090 --> 00:26:31,160
- Gosh, darn it.
- Gosh, darn it, seriously...

454
00:27:03,860 --> 00:27:08,030
Hey. "I was wrong. Please forgive me."

455
00:27:08,300 --> 00:27:12,640
That's all you have to say.
Then I'll forgive you. Got it?

456
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:14,200
Hey!

457
00:27:16,540 --> 00:27:19,080
Hey, I think she's completely
lost her mind.

458
00:27:19,210 --> 00:27:23,050
We barely touched her.
She needs to be taught a real lesson.

459
00:27:23,110 --> 00:27:26,650
This isn't enough to break her spirit.

460
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:30,050
Gosh.

461
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:32,520
- I told you to let me go!
- This wench is crazy.

462
00:27:35,690 --> 00:27:36,790
Seriously!

463
00:27:37,360 --> 00:27:38,560
This darn...

464
00:27:39,030 --> 00:27:40,030
Unbelievable!

465
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:41,800
Seriously!

466
00:27:42,700 --> 00:27:43,770
You've got some nerve!

467
00:27:44,930 --> 00:27:48,000
You think this is your hotel?
You're a murderer!

468
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:56,750
Hey, I think she fainted.

469
00:27:56,950 --> 00:27:59,950
- Passed out? Yes, right. Toss her there.
- Okay.

470
00:28:00,050 --> 00:28:01,150
Gosh...

471
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:29,210
(The First Man)

472
00:28:29,280 --> 00:28:33,650
- Please, save CEO Chae.
- Who are you? What is CEO Chae to you?

473
00:28:33,750 --> 00:28:36,790
Why are you so worked up
and acting so recklessly?

474
00:28:36,990 --> 00:28:38,220
Tae Pyung, now's our chance.

475
00:28:38,320 --> 00:28:41,160
My friend got into crypto and made
a thousand times his investment.

476
00:28:41,220 --> 00:28:42,890
Wait, there's something that lucrative?

477
00:28:43,130 --> 00:28:47,160
You're going to get what you deserve,
in this life and the next.

478
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:51,200
Go on, tell yourself you'll get out.
We'll see about that.

479
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:55,610
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
